snippet.textDisplay: But people seriously don't put your child in a child seat with his/her jacket on. It's dangerous - in case of an accident, the jacket "slips" under the seat belts and the child can fly across the car. The seat belts should always hug the child reasonably tight in order for them to secure properly. So take the jacket off, secure the seat belts and then cover the child with the jacket if the car is still cold.
